caption.text:
2024 is set to see an acceleration of the "quiet outdoors" phenomenon, as brands like Arc'teryx (@arcteryx), Asics (@asics) and Salomon (@salomon) ‚Äî which saw sales skyrocket thanks to the gorpcore obsession with technical clothing such as hiking boots, trail running sneakers and shell jackets ‚Äî look to consolidate their long term appeal to fashion consumers.

As demand for logo-heavy streetwear recedes, these labels are increasingly seeking to elevate their product far beyond the gorpcore niche, by investing fashion collaborations, tapping luxury designers to create more minimalist and fashion forward clothing and courting high-end stockists. It's a shift that has seen niche brands like Roa Hiking @roahiking), Arc'teryx and Mammut (@mammut_swiss1862) worn by coveted tastemakers like #CentralCee (pictured), #Drake and #FrankOcean. 

In 2022, for example, Icelandic outerwear label 66ÀöNorth (@66north) named Kei Toyoshima (@toyoshimakei), a menswear design consultant at Louis Vuitton, as its creative director as part of a push to expand its appeal with fashion consumers. Meanwhile, Arc'teryx CEO Stuart Haselden told BoF earlier this year of the company's plans to invest in its fashion-forward Veilance sub-label, to create luxury staples such as jackets and soft tailoring which benefit from the fabrics and technology used to create the brand's main line outdoor wear.

Is 'quiet outdoors' the new 'quiet luxury'?

caption.text: Yesterday I told you about my passion for #chronographs and my indecision in preferring one dial colour over others. Today, I propose one of the most loved and sought-after configurations in the world of collecting, namely the #pandadial. These are two examples of modern watches that want to recall vintage in different ways, with two or three counters and with mechanical or solar quartz movements. I find them both beautiful and the panda dial in particular extremely iconic and well readable. I have always loved this configuration but perhaps a little too overused. What do you think? Tell me in the comments below.
